{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1516624931,"nonce":"RBml2zWoyxRkTtTXL2f/BUwalrw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyOTA0NTIzNzc=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1680","origin":"github"},"title":"stringtie: prepDE for multiple samples","message":"I'm wondering if the current integration of prepDE.py in the tool is really useful. I guess most users will input a dataset list of sam/bam files where each corresponds to a sample. Currently prepDE.py is called separately for each sample. Hence it seems that it can not be user for differential expression analysis. \n\nA solution might be to generate a separate tool for prepDE that uses all data sets (the gtf output of stringtie) and creates subdirectories for each sample as described in https://ccb.jhu.edu/software/stringtie/index.shtml?t=manual#deseq. \n\nxref. https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1322","files":null}]}